{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:51:20.317134+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 401, "prompt_tokens": 9446, "total_tokens": 9847, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 114, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8960}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "b36fe0c0f33c45b0aa0c347f66592c11", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead82-6e4e-7e52-a010-0d493c4bcd6e-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thank you for reporting this issue. After examining the codebase, I can confirm that the gif profile currently uses a single-pass conversion without palette generation, which is indeed a known limitation.\n\nIn `profiles.toml`, there is already a comment noting this:\n> Note: the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in the issue tracker.\n\nThe `runner.py` file shows that the gif profile applies only fps and scale filters (`-vf fps=...,scale=...:flags=lanczos`) without any palette generation steps.\n\nThis is intentional for simplicity, but as you've observed, it results in color banding. A two‑pass approach (generate palette with `palettegen`, then use it with `paletteuse`) would significantly improve quality, especially for gradients and saturated colors.\n\nWe can keep this issue open as an enhancement request. If you or anyone else would like to contribute a PR that implements two‑pass GIF conversion, we'd be happy to review it.\n\nThanks again for the clear reproduction steps!"}, "id": "call_1d3a11d3744141e681e37ee0", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9446, "output_tokens": 401, "total_tokens": 9847, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 8960}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 114}}}}]}}}
